-- word-count-crystal.cell: crystallization test
-- Oracle: rejoin the split words, should equal original text

⊢ count-words
  given text ≡ "the quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  yield count

  ∴ Count the number of words in «text».
    Words are separated by spaces.

⊢ verify-count
  given count-words→count
  given text ≡ "the quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  yield words-rejoined

  ⊢= words-rejoined ← join(split(text, " "), " ")

  ⊨ words-rejoined = "the quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog"
  ⊨ count-words→count = len(split(text, " "))

⊢ crystallize
  given §count-words
  given verify-count→words-rejoined
  yield §count-words', is-faithful

  ∴ Read «§count-words». It counts words by splitting on spaces.
    Write a ⊢= expression using only Cell primitives that does the same thing.
    The expression should be: len(split(text, " "))

⊢ verify-crystal
  given §count-words'
  given crystallize→is-faithful
  yield approved

  ∴ Does «§count-words'» use only ⊢= primitives?

  ⊨ if approved and crystallize→is-faithful then §count-words' may replace §count-words
